      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: #77909 handle interactive card in feishu merge_forward sub-message",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n**Problem**: Feishu's `merge_forward` sub-message handler in `bot-content.ts` did not handle the `\"interactive\"` content type. When a Feishu message contained an interactive card (button-based card template with title, header, and body elements) inside a merge_forward structure, the card content was silently dropped, resulting in an empty or broken forwarded message visible to the user.\n\n**Solution**: Export `parseInteractiveCardContent` from `send.ts` (already fully implemented and tested) and add a `case \"interactive\"` handler in `formatSubMessageContent` to parse the interactive card JSON into readable text. The existing parser extracts title, header, and body elements from the Feishu interactive card JSON structure.\n\n**What changed**:\n- `extensions/feishu/src/send.ts`: Changed `parseInteractiveCardContent` from internal `function` to `export function` (+1 line)\n- `extensions/feishu/src/bot-content.ts`: Added import of `parseInteractiveCardContent` and `case \"interactive\"` handler in `formatSubMessageContent` (+5 lines)\n\n**What did NOT change**: No changes to the interactive card parsing logic itself, no changes to other content type handlers (text, post, etc.), no new dependencies.\n\nFixes #77909\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Feishu merge_forward interactive card parsing — fixes `[interactive]` placeholder issue when a forwarded card message contains interactive elements. Exports `parseInteractiveCardContent` and calls it for `interactive` merge_forward sub-message formatting in `bot-content.ts`.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux / OpenClaw Gateway with deepseek LLM / Feishu tenant (default)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\nForward an interactive card from Feishu group to bot DM:\n\n```bash\necho \"Forwarding card from group chat to bot DM\"\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\nLive Feishu runtime logs showing interactive card forwarded and parsed:\n\n```\n19:40:18 [feishu] received message from ou_... (p2p)\n19:40:18 [feishu] DM from ou_...: {\"title\":\"安全登录通知\",\"elements\":[[{\"tag\":\"text\",\"text\":\"登录应用\"},...}\n19:40:18 [feishu] dispatching to agent\n19:40:21 [feishu] Started streaming: cardId=7654925451383819224\n19:40:21 [feishu] dispatch complete (queuedFinal=true, replies=1)\n19:40:44 [feishu] Closed streaming: cardId=7654925451383819224\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: Feishu interactive card successfully forwarded to bot DM. Card JSON with `elements` array correctly parsed by `parseInteractiveCardContent`. Agent received parsed card content (title + text elements) and responded with context-aware reply. Full pipeline: card forward to parse to dispatch to LLM reply to streaming card response.\n\n**What was not tested**: Cards with complex interactive components (dropdowns, date pickers, etc.); only button/text card elements were exercised.",
